ated continuously since, finding new and better ways to know and delight customers to earn their lasting loyalty and deliver measurable results.   A GLOBAL FOOTPRINT dunnhumby employs 2,000 people in offices throughout Europe, Asia, Africa, and the Americas. Partnering with transformative, iconic brands across multiple industries including grocery, consumer goods, health, beauty, personal care, food service, apparel, advertising and more.  DIVERSITY AND INCLUSION dunnhumby's spirit of community and the diversity of our people's skills, backgrounds and experiences makes us stronger. We continuously seek to build an environment of inclusion, equality and respect because we know that will make us the best business we can be. DOWNLOAD DUNNHUMBY GENDER PAY REPORT   Speak Speak to your local dunnhumby team today > Close linkedIn Dave Clements Global Retail Director Retail Expert. Over the last 8 years at dunnhumby, Dave has worked with leading retailers and brands across the world, including Tesco, CRV & the Casino Group, to build their customer analytics capability and create transformative customer strategies. Areas of expertise: Retail capability development Customer centricity, loyalty and data analytics programmes Category, marketing and operations transformations across Hypermarkets, Supermarkets, Convenience stores, Pharmacy/Drug, Department Stores and Retail Banks Strategic supplier collaboration Retail sales and revenue growth  linkedIn Jason Nathan Managing Director of Data 20 years of analytical and data experience, of which 17 have been in retail and 12 at dunnhumby, working with both retail and CPG clients across multiple disciplines. Jason serves on the board of our Canada Joint Venture with Metro Canada. Areas of expertise: Category Management, Customer Knowledge, Media & Price solutions Space automation systems Automated range management systems Customer data tooling Multi-channel measurement, tooling and processes  linkedIn Howard Langer Managing Director